These three building blocks unlock a lot of permissionless innovation for Farcaster:

1. If you own an NFT, narrowcast into that collection's community.
2. Feed shows casts from NFT communities you're in.
3. Mint a collection's NFT right from Farcaster.

Eg - one could launch their own followable Topics feature into Farcaster.

- Developer creates a collection of topic entities, maybe nabbing from Google knowledge graph, wikipedia...
- Users follow a topic by minting it from Farcaster (eg - mint 'World news')
- Anyone who mints can cast into Topic, sees related casts.

I wonder if there's an approach where clients earn from the protocol by providing signed impressions and engagements from users (eg likes, comments, etc) back.

It'd motivate clients to deliver a more personalized experience (via better ranking and formats), and would improve relevance of network
Maybe what they earn is actually ad inventory from the protocol. And the impressions / engagements on those ads gets $$ for the client
